<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 11:21AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Band of Heavy Snow Approaching Interstate-15...
At 11:20 AM, radar indicated a band of moderate to heavy snowfall
located along a line from eastern Glacier County, through central
Pondera County at Valier, and into eastern Teton County, moving
southeast at 20 mph. This band of snow is moving towards
Interstate-15, with expected impacts to travel from Dutton to
Shelby, and further west on Highway 2 toward Cut Bank. Snowfall
rates exceeding one inch per hour, with visibility less than one-
half mile are possible within the band of snow. Expect heavier
snowfall rates to continue under this band of snow through at
least noon. Light snow will then continue through this evening.</description>
